rious acoustic feature that allows a person to whisper softly at one side of the cavernous half domed room and for another on the other side to hear every syllable sound is whisked around the semi circular perimeter of the room almost without flaw the phenomenon is known as a whispering gallery link node 36137 image last modified thu 15 mar 2012 at 19 37 read more electrical engineering materials science and engineering stanford engineers weld nanowires with light at the nano level researchers at stanford have discovered a new way to weld together meshes of tiny wires their work could lead to innovative electronics and solar applications to succeed they called upon plasmonics by andrew myers one area of intensive research at the nanoscale is the creation of electrically conductive meshes made of metal nanowires promising exceptional electrical throughput low cost and easy processing engineers foresee a day when such meshes are common in new generations of touch screens video displays light emitting diodes and thin film solar cells link node 36144 image last modified wed 8 feb 2012 at 8 43 read more electrical engineering materials science and engineering stay connected itunes icon google+ icon facebook icon twitter icon linkedin icon syndicate content stanford university school of engineering 475 via ortega stanford california 94305 4121 650.725 1575 1997 2012 stanford university all rights reserved accreditation info terms of use copyright complaints contact us
